[3] Brazil (Bahia)
Date: Tue 31 Mar 2009
Source: La Provincia.es [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.laprovincia.es/secciones/noticia.jsp?pRef=2009033100_5_220381__Sociedad-y-Futuro-Ascienden-muertos-epidemia-dengue-Brasil>


The dengue epidemic, which has affected the Brazilian state of Bahia
(in the northeast) has caused at least 29 deaths and 32 306 [dengue
virus] infections since the beginning of the year [2009], according
to official sources. The number of deaths might be double that, given
that the regional Secretariat of Health indicated that through the
3rd week of March [2009] another 36 suspected dengue deaths are under
investigation. The number of dengue infections is over 305 percent of
the [dengue] infections recorded as of the 3rd week of March of 2007,
according to regional government figures.

In total, 7 cities are in a state of emergency due to the disease and
272 municipalities, about 65 percent [of all municipalities], have
registered at least one case. The [health] authorities fear that
there may be a recrudescence [of dengue virus transmission] within
the next months because the rainy season is now beginning in
northeastern Brazil, a situation that favors the rapid multiplication
of the mosquito [vector].

--
